The paper discusses vulnerabilities in password managers and proposes a new design to minimize and decentralize trust. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the implementation of the proposed design using a Firefox add-on, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The use of secret-sharing and cuckoo hashing techniques to ensure privacy and resilience to offline attacks falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the compatibility of the proposed technique with login forms, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.SI) and programming languages (cs.PL) as it involves modifying POST requests.
